HEADWORD: Nicotiana
<hw>Ni*co`ti*a"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Nicotian</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of American
and Asiatic solanaceous herbs, with viscid foliage and funnel-shaped
blossoms. Several species yield tobacco. See <er>Tobacco</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

